radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT ABD & PELVIS W & W/O CONTRAST, ADDL SECTIONS
radiographic_examinations.findings: The bases of the lungs are clear. There is no pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesion or intrahepatic biliary duct dilation. The portal vein is patent. The nondistended gallbladder is within normal limits, without wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid. The spleen is homogeneous and normal in size. There is minimal haziness between the head of the pancreas and the duodenum. No focal lesions, masses, pancreatic calculi, or pancreatic ductal dilatation are identified. The kidneys demonstrate symmetric nephrograms and excrete contrast promptly. The stomach is unremarkable, without obvious intraluminal mass or wall thickening. The small and large bowel are within normal limits. The aorta is normal in caliber, with mild atherosclerotic calcifications. No pelvic wall or inguinal lymph node enlargement by CT size criteria is seen. There is no pelvic free fluid. No focal lesion suspicious for malignancy present.
